regex pattern searching
metacharacters

can search for character class - [+\-*/]
    searches for the arithmetic operators

uses the re.compile(r'{your search}')              the r in front of the string cancels out special characters

.    - any character except new line

\d   - detects digits (0-9)
\w   - Word Character (a-z, A-Z, 0-9)
\W   - Not a word character
\s   -Whitespace, (space, tab, newline)
\S   - Not whitespace

\b   - word boundary, whitespace or a non alphanumeric character
            will be useful for searching for operators, +-*/
\B   - Not a word boundary

^    - Beginning of a string
$    - End of a string

[]   - Matches characters in brackets
[^ ] - Matches Characters not in brackets

